The '''Conclave on Yavin 4''' was held in the [[Grand Audience Chamber]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] in [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]]. It was called by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] to debate and decide on a unified approach to resisting the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]].

Of all the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], [[Kyp Durron]] was the last to arrive on the jungle [[Moon/Legends|moon]], trying to signal that he wasn't merely doing the bidding of Skywalker. Durron spearheaded a faction favoring more aggressive action against the Yuuzhan Vong, and so came prepared to confront Skywalker. His side made up of around two-thirds of the adult Jedi, including about half of the non-[[Human/Legends|Human]] Jedi.

Luke favored more defensive action against the Vong, but in a surprising move, did not confront Kyp immediately, rather inviting him to share his first-hand insights on the Vong gained while leading the [[Kyp's Dozen|Dozen-and-Two Avengers]]. While a unified policy was not fully decided on, a number of missions were allocated to small teams of Jedi.

